lead_paragraph: The Report of the Exhibition of the Queen's County Agricultural Society, with the address of Hon. JOHN A. DIX, which we publish this morning, will be read with general interest. The occasion was one of great attractiveness. The Society is well organized and vigorously sustained. Agriculture has few more zealous or intelligent friends in this county than its President, JOHN A. KING.
